Header: North Korean leader supervises testing of multiple rocket launchers
Content: North Korea’s state-run television KRT released several still photographs of leader Kim Jong Un supervising a military drill.KRT said North Korea conducted a “strike drill” for multiple launchers, firing tactical guided weapons into the East Sea. The purpose of the drill was to test performance of “large-caliber long-range multiple rocket launchers and tactical guided weapons by defense units,” the state media said.Military experts said the tactical guided weapons could be a short-range, ground-to-ground ballistic missiles.
